                            <comment id="17955893" author="hakuseki" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2025 13:01:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe I&apos;m doing something completely wrong, &#175;&lt;em&gt;(&#12484;)&lt;/em&gt;/&#175;&#8230;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have tried using the EndpointRouteBuilder and RouteBuilder with a hardcoded value as well as a dynamic value but it fails every time&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
                .toD(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;salesforce:bulk2GetQueryJobResults&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                        + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;?jobId=${variable.jobId}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                        + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;amp;maxRecords=2000&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                        + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;amp;locator=ABCDEFGHIJ&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;.&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
                .toD(salesforce(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;bulk2GetQueryJobResults&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
                        .jobId(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;${variable.jobId}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
                        .maxRecords(2000)
                        .locator(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ABCDEFGHIJKL&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;.&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17993136" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 3 Jul 2025 18:02:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks so it seems those parameters was missing in some code that takes those from the endpoint config. You can as workaround provide the values via headers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
